[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating serialization testing**\n\nI'm thinking about how a test may be accepted if it reaches call sites, but high coverage integration requires all call sites. I don't want to risk a serialization script unnecessarily. Dynamic call sites in writeObject and readObject are activated regardless. It might be best to invoke readObject only if the class is deserialized. \n\nI feel like using a method for serialization that reinitializes a cache could help, verifying it efficiently avoids unnecessary loading. However, I'm concerned about writing empty maps and ensuring coverage, especially since the ObjectOutputStream writes this empty map.\n\n**Analyzing module script behavior**\n\nI'm examining the behavior of the provider's getModuleScript call. It seems to always return the moduleSourceProvider, even when using a cached source, because it goes through validation. On the second call, it should return NOT_MODIFIED. \n\nI wonder if using a static AtomicInteger could help track this, but maybe it's not necessary. I need to check if the second returned object is the same as the first one. For NOT_MODIFIED, it's interesting that it returns cachedModule1.getModule() for each getLoadedModule call, leading to a new ModuleScript.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0c945750247f27580169f4f3773c9c8190864a4868b790e43a\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9POLVLH2fRhOVDt9K82yrToXszxc-L6IhjMo1qX6Jalo_xAW91A97bz6j1g0OmnzYbrOOIe-kEywMbENy7lToxU_YR_UY85cRqmZbxnEdz5aQZEsFbpfmshoaBirm69_5mFV-dWo5lJ-C7TMhB3CX1hibns6VtGF-zk1Ail8I_wp5Ny_Ccp741weuVeBcEdmE1K4BU5kC0D35dfkU0fFAtNvRkn9-0z_mdJ2RLDGCb83iz80RpRK5RR_RjzUFl7Z5Y_GszK9q-e4y0niTTfx86lN9WeXXqra0jAROpDbioOHuFUc4kQH86irCXkXnrYshm7mvWOQDDL4e0NVcHorM-_ynzzqH4JDza5n_SDHwgidWFUswpHKLgy3wpAJa4eq2eq26I6H7r3ZZdB-VKjfZ_Rwav8xAsToUOGUg6AsibrLPpNRgMQcZhJ3OxDkHytMWsbBMzDVmDOnJduq1SYglzWXr-CktAQBr-ebEr-hn0tFdwhB_c1hHkeA